<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000008#    01#        506.2#">Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-506.2</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_8.01-506.2"/><heading><desig>§ 8.01-506.2.</desig><title>Proceedings in court of county or city where execution debtor resides</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><bodyText><p>When pursuant to subsection B of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-506"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-506">§ 8.01-506<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          506#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, a summons requires the execution debtor to appear before a court of the county or city in which the execution debtor resides, or of a county or city contiguous thereto, the execution creditor may have the case filed or docketed in that court as follows:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The execution creditor shall file with that court an abstract of the judgment rendered.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The execution creditor shall pay a fee to that court in accordance with the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-69.48:2"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-69.48:2">§ 16.1-69.48:2<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#958#0000000016#0000000001#     69.48#0000000002#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or subdivision 17 of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275">§ 17.1-275<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#          275#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_3"/><heading><desig>3.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> After docketing or filing the abstract of judgment and payment of any fees, the court shall issue the summons and any subsequent executions on the filed or docketed judgment, including a subpoena duces tecum pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-506.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-506.1">§ 8.01-506.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#        506.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and shall conduct such hearings and enter such orders pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-507"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-507">§§ 8.01-507<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          507#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-507.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-507.1">8.01-507.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#        507.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-508"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-508">8.01-508<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          508#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-509"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-509">8.01-509<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          509#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-510"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-510">8.01-510<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          510#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> as may be required.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_4"/><heading><desig>4.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The execution creditor shall file in both courts any releases or satisfactions of judgment.</p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2005 VA CH 726"><content><span normalizedCite="2005 Va. Ch. 726">2005, c. 726<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2005#000726#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVF0-004G-K4BG-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 8.01.</desig><title>CIVIL REMEDIES AND PROCEDURE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 18.</desig><title>EXECUTIONS AND OTHER MEANS OF RECOVERY</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 6.</desig><title>INTERROGATORIES</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Civil Procedure</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MzUxNjJDMEQ5N0YwNDMzM0JDMjEzM0UzOTYzMzI3OTU7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QTlCMjk5M0MwMDE5NDlFNjhFNjQwMUFFNkFDNDNBQjM7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OUEwNkEyNUM0QzQ3NDc2M0IzQzYxNEY2NjNDQUE1Mjk</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Writs of Execution</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QTkyMkZEMTQyOERGNDEwRUExNTg4OEYxMTJEMUNGODI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OUEwNkEyNUM0QzQ3NDc2M0IzQzYxNEY2NjNDQUE1Mjk</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Governments</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MjdEQjE4OUJDMzQxNDNEMEI0RTI1QUFCMzJENjEwRTA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Finance</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MjMzOTBBRTg2MUVDNDdDNUE1M0QxNDk1RERCNjNCN0I7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6Njg1MkM3RkYyNzIxNEVFRkJFMTI2NUM4NUU1ODdEM0Q</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem></classification><classificationGroup classificationScheme="indexing-terms"><classification classificationScheme="legal"/></classificationGroup></metadata></legislativeDoc>